						<div class="postbody">I've got some little questions about writing C in CC65:<br /><br />Somewhere I read: &quot;Use the array operator [] even for pointers&quot;<br />Why should this be done? And in what situation does it produce a difference?<br /><br />Are local static variables slower or less effective than global ones? Or is there no difference at all?</div>

					
