				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think...<br />With -r compiler command...<br />cc65 replaces (non-static) local variables with C variables if it can. But...<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">There is some overhead involved with register variables, since the old contents of the registers must be saved and restored. </div><br /><br />Apparently, <s>non-static</s> STATIC local variables are faster.<br /><br /><s>And &#40;I may be wrong&#41;, I think [] arrays can index like this... Address, x. Whereas pointers always compile into an indirect &#40;Address&#41;, y which is slower.</s><br /><br />Edit: I can't seem to find any examples/documentation to back that up.</div>

					
