					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I ran a few tests...<br /><br />Static Local Variables code was slightly faster than non-static. Reason = <br />-Non-static Variables, lda value, sta RAM, lda RAM later when it's called -- <br />-Static Variables, the value is a constant, it only lda from address of constant when it's called.<br /><br /><br />array [index] vs *(array+index)...<br /><br />All tests I did where essentially equivalent....<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;ldy&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;_index<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;#&lt;(_array)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;ldx&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;#&gt;(_array)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp; ptr1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;stx&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;ptr1+1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(ptr1),y</div></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
